<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/9–1247:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-12T16:00:00+01:00">September 12, 1947—4 p. m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>3714. At a meeting last night of the entire Committee of
                                    Cooperation the delegates were informed by Franks of the results
                                    of our meeting with the Executive Committee, reported my 3709,
                                    September 12, 1 p. m. The Cooperation Committee decided to
                                    postpone the formal meeting of the conference called to receive
                                    the report until September 20–22, the exact date to be
                                    determined later.</p>
                                <p>Sent Department 3714, repeated London for Clayton and Douglas
                                    729.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>